item.title: About
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Great People! Great Jobs! Great Service!

Since 2014, GOSS has focused on forming lasting relationships with companies, organizations and job candidates throughout Texas. We know that when we bring great candidates to great companies, everyone wins. Our clients range from small offices to large corporations and government organizations all over Texas. And, our candidates range from highly experienced full-time professionals to entry-level employees. Whether you want to hire a new employee or just need supplemental temporary employees, Evins Personnel has great employees to meet your needs. Evins is a true full-service human-resources service company. Our services include:
  • Direct Hire Recruiting
  • Temporary Staffing
  • Contract Staffing
  • “Temp-to-hire” Placement
  • Medical Staffing
  • Managed-Vendor Services
  • Human Resources Outsourcing
  • Complete Payroll Servicing
  • HR Consulting
  • Pre-employment Testing
  • On-site Vendor Services
Texas-owned and Texas-operated, GOSS literally has decades of experience, and a strong commitment to the communities we serve. We have developed exceptional connections and relationships with employers throughout Texas. Our strong work ethic and consistent high performance have enabled us to use our local knowledge and experience to match great employees with great employers. We BELIEVE in great service EVERY time! We LISTEN to our clients’ needs. We MEET each of our candidates. We ASK the right questions. And, we DELIVER results. Contact a GOSS office today and let us help you!

item.title: Client Services
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Recruiting Great people Is Our Job!

We know you’re busy. You have a business to run, projects to manage, deadlines to meet, and orders to fill. On top of that, you need to hire great employees – people with proven skills, the right experience and the hard-to-find intangibles that will help them be successful at your company. Let us take care of that for you! Call GOSS! The GOSS team has more than 200 years of combined recruiting and staffing experience. That is a lot of experience. Let us take care of your staffing and hiring process. We are experts in sourcing talent. We deliver great results, through personalized recruitment and staffing solutions. The result is that you hire the best talent, reduce your hiring risks, shift your liability costs, improve your productivity and find running your business easier. You win all the way around. The GOSS “Right Hire” Guarantee Direct hire – when you hire an GOSS candidate you have an on-the-job evaluation period to make sure you are completely satisfied with your new hire. If he or she is not the right person for the role, for any reason, we will provide a replacement candidate free of charge. Temporary-to-hire – If you are not 100-percent satisfied with a temporary-to-hire placement, let us know by the end of the first week, and we will provide a replacement candidate promptly. You will not be billed for the first eight hours worked. Temporary staffing – If you are not 100-percent satisfied with a temporary employee, just let us know by the end of the first day, and we will find you a new employee. You will not be billed for the original temporary employee. As a full-service staffing and recruiting firm, we have solutions for all of your staffing needs. There’s more to a partnership with GOSS Personnel. We also …
  • Provide insight into the job market, hiring and salary trends
  • Create a strategic hiring plan that will save you money and time
  • Perform background checks and pre-employment skills testing
Make GOSS Your HR Partner GOSS’ recruitment professionals know to listen and deliver results – great people and great service. Our tenured staff takes the time to learn about your company and your specific needs. Every business is different, but all need employees with the right combination of skills and experience to get the job done. GOSS helps by conducting a thorough evaluation of your business operations, then designing a recruitment plan that aligns with your needs. We are experts in understanding your business and the workforce challenges you face. GOSS uses cutting-edge assessment tools and testing systems to evaluate, recruit, and hire great employees for you. But, it is not just our tools and processes; it also is the pride our staff takes in making a great placement that helps your company be even more successful. Our dedication to great service, quality processes and, ultimately, your satisfaction make us a great partner. We diligently work to understand and meet your changing workplace demands. We are on your side and always are available, 24 hours a day, seven days a week, 365 days a year. GOSS offers a full complement of professional recruiting services Direct Hire and Executive-Level Recruitment can be faster and pain free. Send us the position requirements, and we recruit, prescreen, and offer only those candidates who match your criteria. Once you have selected possible candidates, we arrange interviews, share feedback, check references, negotiate salaries, and facilitate the entire placement process. GOSS conducts Nationwide Candidate Searches, handles in-depth interviews, conducts behavioral and performance skill assessments, and provides skill-specific presentations of the most qualified candidates. Temporary-To-Hire – Reduce hiring errors through our “temp-to-hire” program that allows you to evaluate a potential new employee on a trial basis. When you feel there is a match, just let us know and we will make the transition to your staff payroll easy. When an employment offer is extended you may complete the 750 temporary-to-hire period or buy it out. Temporary Staffing and Temp-to-Hire Placement give you flexibility, whether you have an unexpected increase in business, need to fill a temporary vacancy, or require additional staff to help complete a special project. GOSS eliminates all of the prescreening for you and only shares candidates we feel would complement your business and fulfill the objectives that you are seeking to accomplish. As a temporary employee, the individual is on our payroll, so we assume responsibility for all payroll taxes, government reporting, disability claims, workers’ compensation, unemployment claims, and W2s. Your bill rate is inclusive of the candidate’s salary as well as the relevant taxes and our administrative fee. Payroll Services are much like our temporary and temp-to-hire program, but you refer the individual to us. Many companies payroll short-term employees and project teams for extended periods to reduce their administrative burden and costs. Make GOSS Your HR Partner You’ll benefit from our years of experience and knowledge of the local business community. We’re not a small, satellite branch of a national corporation, but a locally owned and operated organization. We’re proud of the longevity of our recruiting team, and of the quality solutions we provide. GOSS will customize a strategic workforce plan that focuses on solving the key business challenges you face. We’re experienced pros with proven operations and business savvy. On-site Programs – A large-scale, flexible workforce demands a lot of time to manage. GOSS can oversee the administration of your entire flexible workforce with our on-site programs customized to your needs. We provide supervisory or HR representatives to work at your location. They will assist in evaluating your staffing requirements, accurately managing your staffing needs and monitoring worker performance to ensure productivity and continuous improvement. Managed Service Provider – Simplify your use of staffing across multiple locations, skills, and vendors. GOSS acts as a central point of coordination and accountability for our own employees as well as other vendors’, to improve talent sourcing, selection, retention and productivity. Temporary and Contract Staffing – Do you need great employees for a day, week or year? GOSS can resolve your short- and long-term temporary staffing needs with prescreened and skill-qualified workers. GOSS can minimize your time spent in necessary employee processes by overseeing, tracking, coaching, counseling and supervising a large number of temporary employees. Our program is designed to maintain an optimum, flexible level of staffing for your company. How do we know we’re doing it right? We have the knowledge, the connections, the experience and the tools. Plus, a high percentage of our temporary employees get hired permanently by our clients. We know how to match the right people with the right opportunity. Why go anywhere else? GOSS fills positions in the following fields:
  • Accounting / Financial
  • Administrative (Executive and General)
  • Assembly (Technical and General)
  • Customer Service
  • Call Center
  • Office / Clerical
  • Data Entry
  • Engineering
  • Dental
  • Executive / Managerial
  • Financial Services / Banking
  • Human Resources
  • Healthcare
  • IT Consulting
  • Technical
  • Legal
  • Programming
  • Manufacturing
  • Medical
  • Mortgage
  • Reception
  • Sales / Marketing

Entry-level to Experienced Professionals

item.title: Candidates
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Great People! Great Jobs! Great Service!

We help great people find great jobs. GOSS works with many of Texas’ most prominent and successful companies. Contact us now to discuss the type of job that is best for you. Whether you are looking for a full-time career position, short-term temporary position, or something in between, GOSS Personnel can help you find your next great job. We offer a wide variety of full-time professional positions, challenging temporary assignments, competitive pay, and opportunities to work with great companies. We can help you start earning immediately, improve your skills, and find that next great position that fits your needs. Direct-Hire Placement If you’re looking for new job opportunities or a career change, GOSS Personnel can help you select your next position. We have the contacts and know-how to get you in the door of the company you want. Temporary-to-Hire Temporary-to-hire positions enable you and the company to try each other out before making a long-term job commitment. Temp-to-Hire positions ensure that the best match is made for both you and the company. And, you get to work quickly! Temporary and Project-Based Assignments Short- and long-term assignments are excellent opportunities for you to develop new skills and learn more about various industries and companies from an insider’s perspective! Recruiting Process We encourage all candidates to sign-up online or you may send a resume to our office by email or via fax. Or call your local GOSS office to set an appointment.
  • Qualified candidates are contacted to schedule a time to come to our office to speak with a recruiter and complete an application. Select candidates are contacted by phone and email. At this point, candidates may be asked to provide more information about their experience and skills.
  • A recruiter evaluates candidates’ qualifications and experience.
  • Finalist candidates are scheduled to interview with the company representatives.
  • Additional interviews may be needed depending on the position.
  • If selected for a position or an assignment, candidates are thoroughly briefed on the company and job specifications, as well as provided any client-specific and safety training.
  • All job offers made are contingent upon the successful completion of background, reference checks and – for certain positions – drug testing.
GOSS is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We value the unique qualities that all staff members offer and appreciate the cultural differences they may bring. We are committed to workforce diversity. For every person there is a job. And we can find yours! Why Be A Temporary Employee? Working on a temporary basis offers you great opportunities with GOSS because you’ll have …
  • Flexibility – you choose when and where you work
  • Choice – select your work schedule from a variety of diverse and challenging assignments
  • Bridge to permanent employment – Many temporary employees move to regular full-time positions at our clients’ sites after showcasing their skills
  • Learning and developing opportunities – gain hands-on experience and learn new skills to build your resume
Who Are Some Of Our Temporary Employees?
  • People seeking full-time employment
  • People re-entering the workforce
  • Recent graduates
  • Returning military
  • Those between jobs and / or changing careers
  • Retirees
GOSS recruits for the many types of positions including:
  • Management
  • Office and Administrative
  • Customer Service and Call Center
  • Accounting and Finance
  • Marketing / Sales
  • Medical / Healthcare
  • Dental
  • Legal
  • Technical
  • Professional
  • Assembly, Production and Distribution
  • Warehouse, Shipping and Logistics
  • Skilled Manufacturing
  • Information Technology
  • Engineering
  • Sales / Marketing
  • Human Resources

Entry-level to Experienced Professionals

item.title: Exceptional Services
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Human Resources Our services span the entire employment process including on-boarding, documentation, employee policies, and unemployment. Employee Benefits From health insurance to 401(k) plans, Exceptional Resource Services’ benefits packages allow small employers to recruit and retain top talent. Stop wasting time shopping for insurance every year.  Access affordable “Fortune 500” employee benefits. You’ll be glad you had Exceptional Resource Services help you. And, your employees will thank you. Risk Management Exceptional Resource Services helps keep your employees safe and protect your business by staying on top of the latest compliance issues for you. Payroll Services Fast and accurate processing of payroll, taxes, and records helps increase your company’s efficiency. Simplify payroll and tax payments. Exceptional Resource Services gives you more time to work on your business. You get …
  • Scalable, turn-key complete human resources solutions
  • Experienced human resources, benefits, payroll and risk management  professionals
  • Freedom from certain employment-related liabilities
  • Professional assistance with compliance (payroll, OSHA, EEOC)
  • Access to professional human resources guidance and materials
  • Claims management
  • Clear, easy-to-read and professionally written employee handbooks, policies, procedures and practices
  • Access to better benefits
  • Reduced turnover
  • Quality benefits and recruiting assistance to attract and retain the best employees
  • More time to focus on your bottom line
  • The opportunity to focus on growing your business faster
